<div class="container mb-5">
  <%= render 'header' %>
  <div class="header__section">
    <h2>Anchor Text Profile</h2>
     <p>Anchor Text refers to the clickable text in a link. Best practice is to have a variety of different types to prevent over optimization, including exact match, partial match, and natural anchors.</p>
   </div>

  <div class="row mb-4">
    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-lg-4">
      <%= render 'panel--anchor-text-ratio' %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-lg-4">
      <%= render 'panel--total-backlinks' %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card panel">
        <div class="panel__title">About Text Ratio</div>
        <p class="text__font-size--14">You want to start off with a healthy number of Natural Links to avoid being penalized by search engines.</p>
        <a href="#" class="text__font-size--14">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>


    <div class="clearfix mb-2">
      <a class="btn btn-link float-right" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseExample" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseExample">
